## Database-Specific Features

### PostgreSQL

```ruby
# Array columns
t.string :tags, array: true, default: []

# JSON columns
t.jsonb :metadata

# UUID columns
enable_extension 'pgcrypto'
create_table :articles, id: :uuid do |t|
  t.string :title
end

# Full-text search
add_index :articles, :title, using: :gin, opclass: :gin_trgm_ops
```

### MySQL

```ruby
# Case-sensitive unique index
add_index :users, :email, unique: true, 
          name: 'index_users_on_email_case_sensitive',
          length: { email: 255 }

# Full-text search
add_index :articles, [:title, :body], type: :fulltext
```

### SQLite

```ruby
# Limited features compared to PostgreSQL/MySQL
# Good for development, not recommended for production

# No array columns
# No jsonb columns
# Limited constraint support
```

